def split_coordinate(coor):
    if(isinstance(coor, float)):
        return coor
    coor = coor.split(', ')
    coor[0] = float(coor[0][1:])
    coor[1] = float(coor[1][:-1])
    return list(coor)

df['Location 1'] = df['Location 1'].apply(lambda x: split_coordinate(x))
df = df.rename(columns = {'Location 1': 'Coordinate'})

def plotit(_year_, _side_):
    fig, ax = plt.subplots(1,1, figsize = (20,5))
    year_df = crime_df.loc[crime_df['Year'] == _year_]
    month_df = year_df.groupby(['Inside/Outside'])['Month'].value_counts().sort_index().to_frame(name = 'count').reset_index()
    
    net = month_df[month_df['Inside/Outside'] == 'Inside']['count'].values - month_df[month_df['Inside/Outside'] == 'Outside']['count'].values
    
    color = []
    if (_side_ == 'All'):
        color = ['darkred', 'salmon']
        line_df = pd.DataFrame(data = {'Net': net}, index = np.unique(df.Month.values, return_index=False))
    else:
        line_df = pd.DataFrame(data = {f'{ _side_} - Growth Rate': month_df[month_df['Inside/Outside'] == _side_]['count'].values}, index = np.unique(df.Month.values, return_index=False))[f'{ _side_} - Growth Rate'].pct_change(periods= 1)
        line_df[0] = 0
        if (_side_ == 'Inside'):
            color = ['darkred', 'grey']    
        else:
            color = ['grey', 'salmon']
    ax = sns.barplot(data = month_df,
                     x = 'Month',
                     y = 'count',
                     hue = 'Inside/Outside',
                     palette= color,)
    ax2 = ax.twinx()
    line_df.plot.line(linewidth = 3, marker = 'o', color = 'dodgerblue', ax = ax2, markersize = 8)
    ax.legend(bbox_to_anchor=(0.08, 1))
    ax2.legend(bbox_to_anchor=(1, 1))

df['Day of Week'] = df['CrimeDate'].astype('datetime64[ns]').dt.day_name()
df['CrimeTime'] = pd.to_datetime(df['CrimeTime'], format='%H', exact=False).astype(str).str[11:16]
df['Hour'] = df['CrimeTime'].astype('datetime64[ns]').dt.hour
WeekDays = ['Sunday', 'Saturday', 'Friday', 'Thursday', 'Wednesday', 'Tuesday','Monday']
Hours = np.arange(24)
gb = df.groupby(['Day of Week', 'Hour']).size()
Crime_Weekdays_df = pd.DataFrame(columns = WeekDays, index= Hours)

    Crime_Weekdays_df[col] = [x for x in gb[col]]
df = df.drop(columns= ['Day of Week','Hour'])

def checkContinuous(col):
    date_diff = np.diff(col.sort_values().unique()).astype('timedelta64[D]')
    if np.all(date_diff == np.timedelta64(1, 'D')):
        print('Dates are continuous.')
    else:
        print('Dates are not continuous.')
    return np.all(date_diff == np.timedelta64(1, 'D'))

Chui thi gian thng c 4 thnh phn chnh:

  • Thnh phn xu th (trend) - T: th hin tng hay gim ca chui thi gian trong tng lai.
  • Thnh phn ma v (seasonality) - S: th hin cho s lp li ca chui thi gian theo chu k.
  • Thnh phn chu k (cyclical) - C
  • Thnh phn ngu nhin (random) - R hay error

Ta s s dng 2 phng php phn tch thnh phn ca chui thi gian:

  • Phng php phn tch chui thi gian theo m hnh nhn
  • Phng php phn tch chui thi gian theo m hnh cng

Multiplicative Decomposition: Mô hình nhân¶

$$Y_t = T_t S_t C_t R_t$$
In [ ]:
mul_model = seasonal_decompose(crime_count['CrimeCount'], model='multiplicative', extrapolate_trend='freq')

plt.rcParams.update({'figure.figsize': (8,8)})

Additive Decomposition: Mô hình cộng¶

$$Y_t = T_t + S_t + C_t + R_t$$
In [ ]:
add_model = seasonal_decompose(crime_count['CrimeCount'], model='additive', extrapolate_trend='freq')

fig2 = add_model.plot()
fig2.axes[0].set_ylabel('Observed')

plt.show()

Qua 2 phng php phn tch thnh phn, ta thy c rng chui c tnh ma v vi chu k l 1 nm, bt u t thng 2 nm ny n thng 2 nm sau.

T tng quan (ACF - Autocorrelation Function)

  • Cc gi tr trong chui thi gian hu nh c s tng quan vi gi tr tr ca n, cc gi tr cng gn nhau th tng quan cng mnh hoc cc gi tr cng thuc 1 chu k thng s c tng quan cao (cng thng trong chu k nm hoc cng qu trong chu k nm).
  • H s t tng quan thng c dng tm ra tr ca qu trnh trung bnh trt MV(q) v kim tra cc yu t ma v.
In [ ]:
plt.rcParams.update({'figure.figsize': (8,6)})
ax1 = plot_acf(crime_count)

Trc x l tr, trc y l gi tr ca h s tng quan ng vi tr . Phn mu xanh l khong tin cy 95% gi tr h s t tng quan bng 0. Ta nn chn gi tr q l gi tr u tin m h s tng quan nm ngoi khong tin cy ny. Vy ta s chn q = 1.

T tnq quan ring phn (PACF - Partial Autocorrelation Function)

  • V c bn h s ny cng ging nh h s t tng quan, tuy nhin vn c s khc bit, l h s tng quan ny b qua nh hng ca cc chui tr trung gian (cc chui tr $x_{t-1}, ..., x_{t-k+1}$ nm gia $x_t$ v $x_{t-k}$).
  • PACF c tc dng tm ra h s bc t do p ca qu trnh t hi quy AR(p). Tng t nh ACF, ta s tm c gi tr p thng qua th PACF, chnh l v tr m gi tr ca h s tng quan ring phn nm ngoi ngng tin cy 95%.
In [ ]:
plot_pacf(crime_count);

Quan st biu , ta s chn c gi tr p = 1.

Mô hình ARIMA¶

Da trn gi thuyt chui dng v phng sai khng i. M hnh s dng kt hp hai u vo chnh l nhng tn hiu qu kh ca chui c d bo d bo n. Cc tn hiu bao gm: chui t hi qui AR(auto regression) v chui trung bnh trt MA(moving average).

p dng m hnh ARIMA vi cc tham s p = 1, d = 1, q = 1.

Da vo bng kt qu t m hnh ARIMA, ta c th thy c cc thng s ca m hnh:

  • coef l gi tr h s c lng t m hnh tng ng vi cc bin.
  • std err l lch chun ca h s c lng.
  • P>|z| l gi tr P-value, gi tr P-value < 0.05 s cho thy h s c lng ln hn 95% l c ngha thng k.
  • No. Observations l s lng quan st (s lng mu d liu).
  • Log Likelihood: Ga tr hm logarit c lng hp l ti a.
  • AIC: Ch s Akaike Information Criteria, ch s ny c lng lng thng tin b mt i bi mt m hnh (do d bo sai), m hnh cng mt t thng tin th c cht lng cng cao. Do AIC cng nh th m hnh cng tt.
  • BIC: Ch s Bayesian Information Criteria.

nh gi kt qu ca m hnh trn tp test da vo cc metric ca hi quy tuyn tnh nh: MSE, RMSE, MAE, MAPE.

In [ ]:
def evaluate(y, y_hat):
    e = y-y_hat
    mse=np.round(np.mean(e**2), 3)
    rmse=np.round(np.sqrt(mse), 3)
    mae=np.round(np.mean(np.abs(e)), 3)
    mape=np.round(np.mean(e/y), 3)

    print(f'Mean Square Error: {mse}')
    print(f'Root Mean Square Error: {rmse}')
    print(f'Mean Absolute Error: {mae}')
    print(f'Mean Absolute Percentage Error: {mape}')
    return mse, rmse, mae, mape

evaluate(test.values, fitted_series.values)

Lowess Smooth

  • Loess s dng mt ca s trt (window) tnh ton gi tr xp x ti mi im d liu bng cch ly trung bnh c trng s ca cc quan st trong ca s trt.
  • Thut ton c tnh $y_i$ bi frac*N im d liu gn nht, trong N l s lng im d liu trong mi ca s, v frac l t l ca N. Cc im d liu gn nht c xc nh bng cch tm cc im d liu c khong cch nh nht n $x_i$. Sau , tnh $y_i$ bng trung bnh c trng s ca cc im d liu trong window v di chuyn window sang phi v lp li cc bc tnh ton.
In [ ]:
from statsmodels.nonparametric.smoothers_lowess import lowess

fig, ax = plt.subplots(2, figsize=(20,15))
df_loess_15 = pd.DataFrame(lowess(plot_df.CrimeCount, np.arange(len(plot_df.CrimeCount)), frac=0.15)[:, 1], index=plot_df.index, columns=['CrimeCount'])
df_loess_15.plot(ax=ax[0])
ax[0].set_title('Loess Smoothing (0.15)', fontsize=20, fontweight='bold', pad=15)

df_loess_5 = pd.DataFrame(lowess(plot_df.CrimeCount, np.arange(len(plot_df.CrimeCount)), frac=0.05)[:, 1], index=plot_df.index, columns=['CrimeCount'])
